{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781151252967,"sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AhQqt3WzrLCMCZ3VJnnlOt6h","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","offset":241,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n241:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n242:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n243: \n244:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n245:   outputs:\n246:     config:\n247:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n248:       machineOwned: false\n249:       fields:\n250:         - sessionId\n251:         - parentSessionId\n252:         - lineageMode\n253:         - generation\n254:         - continuedFromRun\n255:         - releaseReadinessState\n256:     findingsRegistry:\n257:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n258:       machineOwned: true\n259:       sections:\n260:         - openFindings\n261:         - resolvedFindings\n262:         - repeatedFindings\n263:         - dimensionCoverage\n264:         - findingsBySeverity\n265:         - convergenceScore\n266:     reviewReport:\n267:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n268:       sections:\n269:         - executive-summary\n270:         - planning-trigger\n271:         - active-finding-registry\n272:         - remediation-workstreams\n273:         - spec-seed\n274:         - plan-seed\n275:         - traceability-status\n276:         - deferred-items\n277:         - audit-appendix\n278:     strategy:\n279:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n280:       requiredSections:\n281:         - topic\n282:         - review-dimensions\n283:         - completed-dimensions\n284:         - running-findings\n285:         - what-worked\n286:         - what-failed\n287:         - exhausted-approaches\n288:         - ruled-out-directions\n289:         - next-focus\n290:         - known-context\n291:         - cross-reference-status\n292:         - files-under-review\n293:         - review-boundaries\n294:     dashboard:\n295:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n296:       machineOwned: true\n297:       sections:\n298:         - status\n299:         - findings-summary\n300:         - dimension-coverage\n301:         - progress\n302:         - next-focus\n303:     pauseSentinel:\n304:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n305:       machineOwned: false\n306:       description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n307:     jsonl:\n308:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n309:       iterationRecord:\n310:         required:\n311:           - type\n312:           - mode\n313:           - run\n314:           - status\n315:           - focus\n316:           - dimensions\n317:           - filesReviewed\n318:           - findingsCount\n319:           - findingsSummary\n320:           - findingsNew\n321:           - findingDetails\n322:           - newFindingsRatio\n323:           - sessionId\n324:           - generation\n325:           - lineageMode\n326:           - timestamp\n327:           - durationMs\n328:         optional:\n329:           - parentSessionId\n330:           - continuedFromRun\n331:           - findingsRefined\n332:           - findingRefs\n333:           - traceabilityChecks\n334:           - coverage\n335:           - noveltyJustification\n336:           - ruledOut\n337:           - focusTrack\n338:           - scoreEstimate\n339:           - segment\n340:           - convergenceSignals\n341:           - graphEvents\n342:       synthesisEvent:\n343:         required:\n344:           - type\n345:           - event\n346:           - mode\n347:           - totalIterations\n348:           - verdict\n349:           - activeP0\n350:           - activeP1\n351:           - activeP2\n352:           - dimensionCoverage\n353:           - stopReason\n354:           - timestamp\n355: \n356: # Render targets define where generated or mixed-authored contract fragments land.\n357: render:\n358:   artifacts:\n359:     - id: workflow-auto\n360:       path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\n361:       ownership: mixed\n362:       format: yaml\n363:       markers:\n364:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n365:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n366:       sections:\n367:         - target-types\n368:         - dimensions\n369:         - verdicts\n370:         - quality-gates\n371:         - convergence\n372:         - cross-reference-protocols\n373:     - id: workflow-confirm\n374:       path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml\n375:       ownership: mixed\n376:       format: yaml\n377:       markers:\n378:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n379:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n380:       sections:\n381:         - target-types\n382:         - dimensions\n383:         - verdicts\n384:         - quality-gates\n385:         - convergence\n386:         - cross-reference-protocols\n387:     - id: agent-opencode\n388:       path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n389:       ownership: mixed\n390:       format: markdown\n391:       markers:\n392:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n393:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n394:       sections:\n395:         - dimensions\n396:         - severities\n397:         - quality-gates\n398:         - cross-reference-protocols\n399:         - outputs\n400:     - id: agent-claude\n401:       path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n402:       ownership: mixed\n403:       format: markdown\n404:       markers:\n405:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n406:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n407:       sections:\n408:         - dimensions\n409:         - severities\n410:         - quality-gates\n411:         - cross-reference-protocols\n412:         - outputs\n413:     - id: agent-codex\n414:       path: .codex/agents/deep-review.toml\n415:       ownership: mixed\n416:       format: toml\n417:       markers:\n418:         begin: \"# BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n419:         end: \"# END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n420:       sections:\n421:         - dimensions\n422:         - severities\n423:         - quality-gates\n424:         - cross-reference-protocols\n425:         - outputs\n426:     - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n427:       path: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n428:       ownership: mixed\n429:       format: markdown\n430:       markers:\n431:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n432:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n433:       sections:\n434:         - target-types\n435:         - dimensions\n436:         - verdicts\n437:         - quality-gates\n438:         - outputs\n439:     - id: review-contract-snapshot\n440:       path: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n441:       ownership: generated\n442:       format: markdown\n443:       markers:\n444:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n445:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n446:       sections:\n447:         - meta\n448:         - target-types\n449:         - dimensions\n450:         - severities\n451:         - verdicts\n452:         - quality-gates\n453:         - convergence\n454:         - cross-reference-protocols\n455:         - outputs\n456:         - validation\n457: \n458: # Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\n459: validation:\n460:   schemaVersion: 1\n461:   checks:\n462:     - id: schema\n463:       description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n464:     - id: render-verify\n465:       description: Re-render downstream artifacts in verify mode and fail on drift.\n466:     - id: marker-integrity\n467:       description: Ensure every render target contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n468:     - id: enum-parity\n469:       description: Ensure target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, and quality gates match across rendered artifacts.\n470:     - id: jsonl-parity\n471:       description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n472:     - id: lifecycle-parity\n473:       description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n474:     - id: reducer-contract\n475:       description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n476:     - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n477:       description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n478:     - id: runtime-coverage\n479:       description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared render artifact and parity coverage.\n480:     - id: playbook-assertions\n481:       description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.\n\n(End of file - total 481 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","text":"      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings\n        - resolvedFindings\n        - repeatedFindings\n        - dimensionCoverage\n        - findingsBySeverity\n        - convergenceScore\n    reviewReport:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n      sections:\n        - executive-summary\n        - planning-trigger\n        - active-finding-registry\n        - remediation-workstreams\n        - spec-seed\n        - plan-seed\n        - traceability-status\n        - deferred-items\n        - audit-appendix\n    strategy:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n      requiredSections:\n        - topic\n        - review-dimensions\n        - completed-dimensions\n        - running-findings\n        - what-worked\n        - what-failed\n        - exhausted-approaches\n        - ruled-out-directions\n        - next-focus\n        - known-context\n        - cross-reference-status\n        - files-under-review\n        - review-boundaries\n    dashboard:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - status\n        - findings-summary\n        - dimension-coverage\n        - progress\n        - next-focus\n    pauseSentinel:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n    jsonl:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n      iterationRecord:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - mode\n          - run\n          - status\n          - focus\n          - dimensions\n          - filesReviewed\n          - findingsCount\n          - findingsSummary\n          - findingsNew\n          - findingDetails\n          - newFindingsRatio\n          - sessionId\n          - generation\n          - lineageMode\n          - timestamp\n          - durationMs\n        optional:\n          - parentSessionId\n          - continuedFromRun\n          - findingsRefined\n          - findingRefs\n          - traceabilityChecks\n          - coverage\n          - noveltyJustification\n          - ruledOut\n          - focusTrack\n          - scoreEstimate\n          - segment\n          - convergenceSignals\n          - graphEvents\n      synthesisEvent:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - event\n          - mode\n          - totalIterations\n          - verdict\n          - activeP0\n          - activeP1\n          - activeP2\n          - dimensionCoverage\n          - stopReason\n          - timestamp\n\n# Render targets define where generated or mixed-authored contract fragments land.\nrender:\n  artifacts:\n    - id: workflow-auto\n      path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: yaml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-auto -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n    - id: workflow-confirm\n      path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_confirm.yaml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: yaml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/workflow-confirm -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n    - id: agent-opencode\n      path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-opencode -->\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: agent-claude\n      path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-claude -->\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: agent-codex\n      path: .codex/agents/deep-review.toml\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: toml\n      markers:\n        begin: \"# BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n        end: \"# END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/agent-codex\"\n      sections:\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - quality-gates\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n    - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n      path: .opencode/skills/deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md\n      ownership: mixed\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/quick-reference-review-mode -->\"\n      sections:\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - outputs\n    - id: review-contract-snapshot\n      path: .opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract_snapshot.md\n      ownership: generated\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n      sections:\n        - meta\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n        - validation\n\n# Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\nvalidation:\n  schemaVersion: 1\n  checks:\n    - id: schema\n      description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n    - id: render-verify\n      description: Re-render downstream artifacts in verify mode and fail on drift.\n    - id: marker-integrity\n      description: Ensure every render target contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n    - id: enum-parity\n      description: Ensure target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, and quality gates match across rendered artifacts.\n    - id: jsonl-parity\n      description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n    - id: lifecycle-parity\n      description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n    - id: reducer-contract\n      description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n    - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n      description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n    - id: runtime-coverage\n      description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared render artifact and parity coverage.\n    - id: playbook-assertions\n      description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.","lineStart":241,"lineEnd":481,"totalLines":481,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/assets/review_mode_contract.yaml","time":{"start":1781151252950,"end":1781151252964}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08254c9624440ac9016a2a3614ec8c8191a03b751dd44e5775"}},"id":"prt_eb4e341d3001PAgUs2Y4qmjogR","sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","messageID":"msg_eb4e3286f001R5pOJm5dL9Vtu4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781151252990,"sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Vj78e0xhfu8f8DXlntpjSz5o","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","offset":241,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n241:     \"P1\": 1,\n242:     \"P2\": 2\n243:   },\n244:   \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n245:   \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n246:   \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n247:   \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n248:   \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n249:   \"graphBlockers\": [],\n250:   \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: This file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n255: \n256: ### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n257: \n258: | Field | Type | Description |\n259: |-------|------|-------------|\n260: | `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n261: | `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n262: | `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n263: | `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n264: | `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n265: \n266: ### Default Values\n267: \n268: When no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\n269: When no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\n270: When JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n271: \n272: ### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n273: \n274: - **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n275: - **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n276: - **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n277: - **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n282: \n283: Write-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n284: \n285: ### Structure\n286: \n287: ```markdown\n288: # Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n289: \n290: ## Focus\n291: [Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n292: \n293: ## Scorecard\n294: - Dimensions covered: [list]\n295: - Files reviewed: [count]\n296: - New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n297: - Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n298: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n299: \n300: ## Findings\n301: \n302: ### P0, Blocker\n303: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n304: \n305: ### P1, Required\n306: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n307: \n308: ### P2, Suggestion\n309: - **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n310: \n311: ## Cross-Reference Results\n312: | Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n313: |----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n314: | spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n315: \n316: ## Assessment\n317: - New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n318: - Dimensions addressed: [list]\n319: - Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n320: \n321: ## Ruled Out\n322: - [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n323: \n324: ## Dead Ends\n325: - [Direction]: [Why]\n326: \n327: ## Recommended Next Focus\n328: [What to investigate next]\n329: ```\n330: \n331: Every finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n336: \n337: The review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n338: \n339: | # | Section | Description |\n340: |---|---------|-------------|\n341: | 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n342: | 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n343: | 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n344: | 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n345: | 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n346: | 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n347: | 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n348: | 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n349: | 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n350: | 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n351: \n352: **Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n353: \n354: **Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n355: \n356: **Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n357: \n358: **Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n359: \n360: **Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n361: \n362: **Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n363: \n364: **Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n365: \n366: **Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n367: \n368: **Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n369: \n370: ---\n371: \n372: ## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n373: \n374: Auto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n375: \n376: - **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n377: - **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n378: - **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n379: - **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n380: \n381: ### Sections\n382: \n383: | Section | Source | Description |\n384: |---------|--------|-------------|\n385: | Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n386: | Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n387: | Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n388: | Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n389: \n390: **Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n395: \n396: Every new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n397: \n398: ### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n399: \n400: Embed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n401: \n402: ```json\n403: {\n404:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n405:   \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n406:   \"evidenceRefs\": [\n407:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n408:     \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n409:   ],\n410:   \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n411:   \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n412:   \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n413:   \"confidence\": 0.86,\n414:   \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n415:   \"transitions\": [\n416:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n417:   ]\n418: }\n419: ```\n420: \n421: ### Required Fields\n422: \n423: | Field | Type | Description |\n424: |-------|------|-------------|\n425: | `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n426: | `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n427: | `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n428: | `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n429: | `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n430: | `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n431: | `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n432: | `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n433: | `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n434: \n435: ### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n436: \n437: 1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n438: 2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n439: 3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n440: 4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n441: 5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n442: \n443: ### Severity Transition Rules\n444: \n445: - **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n446: - **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n447: - **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n448: - Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n453: \n454: Each finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n455: \n456: ### Schema\n457: \n458: ```json\n459: {\n460:   \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n461:   \"severity\": \"P1\",\n462:   \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n463:   \"status\": \"active\",\n464:   \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n465:   \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n466:   \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\",\n467:   \"line\": 955,\n468:   \"firstSeen\": 2,\n469:   \"lastSeen\": 4,\n470:   \"transitions\": [\n471:     { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n472:     { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n473:   ]\n474: }\n475: ```\n476: \n477: | Field | Type | Description |\n478: |-------|------|-------------|\n479: | findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n480: | severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n481: | category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n482: | status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n483: | dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n484: | title | string | Short description |\n485: | file | string | File path |\n486: | line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n487: | firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n488: | transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n489: \n490: ### Status Lifecycle\n491: \n492: ```text\n493: [discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n494:                   |\n495:                   +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n496:                   |\n497:                   +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n498: ```\n499: \n500: | Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n501: |--------|----------------------|\n502: | active | Yes |\n503: | resolved | No |\n504: | deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n505: | disproved | No |\n506: \n507: ### Deduplication\n508: \n509: Same file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n510: \n511: ### Cross-Reference Protocols\n512: \n513: | Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n514: |----------|-------|------------|------|\n515: | spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n516: | checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n517: | skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n518: | agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n519: | feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n520: | playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n521: \n522: Severity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n523: - `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n524: - `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n525: - `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n526: \n527: ### Quality Gates\n528: \n529: | Gate | Rule |\n530: |------|------|\n531: | Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n532: | Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n533: | Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n534: \n535: All three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.\n\n(End of file - total 535 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}\n```\n\nThis file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n\n### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","text":"    \"P1\": 1,\n    \"P2\": 2\n  },\n  \"openFindingsCount\": 3,\n  \"resolvedFindingsCount\": 1,\n  \"convergenceScore\": 0.44,\n  \"graphConvergenceScore\": 1.01,\n  \"graphDecision\": \"STOP_ALLOWED\",\n  \"graphBlockers\": [],\n  \"corruptionWarnings\": []\n}\n```\n\nThis file is machine-owned and must stay synchronized with the latest iteration delta, dashboard metrics, and synthesized review report.\n\n### Blocked-Stop and Corruption-Tracking Additions\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `blockedStopHistory` | array | One entry per `blocked_stop` JSONL event: `{run, blockedBy, gateResults, recoveryStrategy, timestamp}`. Rendered in the dashboard `BLOCKED STOPS` section and can drive the strategy `next-focus` anchor when blocked-stop is the most recent loop event. |\n| `persistentSameSeverity` | array | Findings observed in ≥2 iterations with NO severity transitions beyond initial discovery. REQ-018 split of the deprecated `repeatedFindings` bucket. |\n| `severityChanged` | array | Findings that went through at least one severity transition (P0↔P1↔P2) in their `transitions` history. |\n| `repeatedFindings` | array | **Deprecated.** Union of `persistentSameSeverity` and `severityChanged`. Retained for backward compatibility, new code should read the split arrays. |\n| `corruptionWarnings` | array | Per-line corruption reports from `parseJsonlDetailed()`: `{line, raw, error}`. Non-empty means the reducer detected malformed JSONL. |\n\n### Default Values\n\nWhen no `graph_convergence` event has been recorded yet, defaults are `graphConvergenceScore: 0`, `graphDecision: null`, and `graphBlockers: []`.\nWhen no `blocked_stop` event has been recorded yet, `blockedStopHistory: []`.\nWhen JSONL parses cleanly, `corruptionWarnings: []`.\n\n### Fail-Closed Semantics (REQ-015, REQ-016)\n\n- **Malformed JSONL**: The reducer CLI exits with code `2` and writes a warning to stderr when `corruptionWarnings.length > 0`. Pass `--lenient` (or `lenient:true` to `reduceReviewState`) to escape-hatch out and preserve the v1.2.0.0 fail-open behavior for legacy packets.\n- **Missing machine-owned anchors**: `replaceAnchorSection()` throws `Error('Missing machine-owned anchor \"<id>\" in deep-review strategy file.')` when the strategy file is present but lacks one of the required anchors. Pass `--create-missing-anchors` (or `createMissingAnchors:true`) to bootstrap empty strategy files by appending the missing anchor blocks.\n- **Dashboard surfaces**: `CORRUPTION WARNINGS` section lists detected lines. `BLOCKED STOPS` section lists `blockedStopHistory` entries. `GRAPH CONVERGENCE` section reports `graphConvergenceScore` / `graphDecision` / `graphBlockers`.\n- **Strategy next-focus override**: When the latest `blocked_stop` event timestamp is newer than the latest iteration timestamp, the reducer rewrites the strategy `next-focus` anchor to surface the blocking gates and recovery hint so operators see the blocker before choosing the next iteration direction.\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION FILES (review/iterations/iteration-NNN.md)\n\nWrite-once files. One per iteration, zero-padded 3-digit naming.\n\n### Structure\n\n```markdown\n# Iteration [N]: [Focus Area]\n\n## Focus\n[Dimension(s), files, scope investigated]\n\n## Scorecard\n- Dimensions covered: [list]\n- Files reviewed: [count]\n- New findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- Refined findings: P0=[n] P1=[n] P2=[n]\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n\n## Findings\n\n### P0, Blocker\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P1, Required\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n### P2, Suggestion\n- **F[NNN]**: [Title], `file:line`, [Description with evidence]\n\n## Cross-Reference Results\n| Protocol | Status | Gate | Evidence | Notes |\n|----------|--------|------|----------|-------|\n| spec_code | pass/partial/fail | hard | file:line | ... |\n\n## Assessment\n- New findings ratio: [0.0-1.0]\n- Dimensions addressed: [list]\n- Novelty justification: [breakdown]\n\n## Ruled Out\n- [Approach]: [Why], [Evidence]\n\n## Dead Ends\n- [Direction]: [Why]\n\n## Recommended Next Focus\n[What to investigate next]\n```\n\nEvery finding must include: unique ID (`F001`...), severity (`P0`/`P1`/`P2`), concrete `file:line` evidence, and dimension tag.\n\n---\n\n## 7. REVIEW REPORT (review/review-report.md)\n\nThe review synthesis output contains 9 core sections plus a conditional `## Resource Map Coverage Gate` section when `resource_map_present` is true:\n\n| # | Section | Description |\n|---|---------|-------------|\n| 1 | Executive Summary | Verdict, active P0/P1/P2 counts, scope, `hasAdvisories` flag |\n| 2 | Planning Trigger | Why result routes to planning or changelog |\n| 3 | Active Finding Registry | Deduped active findings with evidence, severity, dimension |\n| 4 | Remediation Workstreams | Ordered lanes grouped by dependency or area |\n| 5 | Spec Seed | Minimal spec updates implied by findings |\n| 6 | Plan Seed | Initial remediation tasks from findings |\n| 7 | Traceability Status | Core vs overlay protocol outcomes and gaps |\n| 8 | Resource Map Coverage Gate | Present only when `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` existed at init, contains touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map |\n| 9 | Deferred Items | Advisory findings, blocked items, follow-up checks |\n| 10 | Audit Appendix | Coverage, convergence replay, audit detail |\n\n**Executive Summary** includes verdict (`PASS`/`CONDITIONAL`/`FAIL`), active finding counts, `hasAdvisories` boolean (PASS + P2 > 0), scope description, and convergence reason.\n\n**Planning Trigger** routes FAIL/CONDITIONAL to remediation planning, PASS to changelog creation.\n\n**Active Finding Registry** lists each active finding with findingId, severity, dimension, title, file:line evidence, first/last seen iteration, and status.\n\n**Remediation Workstreams** group related findings into ordered lanes with constituent finding IDs and execution order.\n\n**Spec Seed / Plan Seed** provide minimal spec updates and initial remediation tasks referencing finding IDs and target files.\n\n**Traceability Status** reports per-protocol pass/partial/fail with gating class and evidence.\n\n**Resource Map Coverage Gate** is emitted only when `resource_map_present` is true and MUST contain exactly three bullets: touched entries, untouched entries (`expected-by-scope` vs `gap`), and implementation paths absent from the map.\n\n**Deferred Items** captures advisory findings, blocked protocols, and future follow-up checks.\n\n**Audit Appendix** contains iteration table, convergence signal replay, file coverage matrix, and dimension breakdown.\n\n---\n\n## 8. DASHBOARD (review/deep-review-dashboard.md)\n\nAuto-generated summary. Never manually edited.\n\n- **Path**: `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated from**: JSONL state log + strategy + findings registry\n- **Refresh**: Regenerated after every iteration\n- **Protection**: `auto-generated` in fileProtection\n\n### Sections\n\n| Section | Source | Description |\n|---------|--------|-------------|\n| Findings Summary | JSONL | Active P0/P1/P2 counts, new vs refined |\n| Progress Table | JSONL | Run, status, focus, dimensions, ratio, duration |\n| Coverage | Strategy + JSONL | Dimension completion, file coverage, protocol status |\n| Trend | JSONL signals | Rolling average, composite stop score, trajectory |\n\n**Rules:** Sole inputs are JSONL + strategy. Overwrite entirely on refresh. Read-only for all agents.\n\n---\n\n## 9. CLAIM ADJUDICATION\n\nEvery new P0/P1 finding must carry a **typed claim-adjudication packet**. The packet is parsed by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication` in the review workflow and its pass/fail result is persisted as a `claim_adjudication` event in `deep-review-state.jsonl`. The next iteration's `step_check_convergence` legal-stop decision tree reads the latest event via `claimAdjudicationGate` (gate `f`), a missing or failed packet vetoes STOP even if every other gate passes. Prose-only adjudication blocks are no longer accepted.\n\n### Typed Packet Schema (required)\n\nEmbed the packet inside the iteration file for each new P0/P1 finding. The orchestrator parses it after evaluation and persists the validation result.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"claim\": \"Coverage-graph upsert identity is bare `id`, so cross-session collisions overwrite prior rows.\",\n  \"evidenceRefs\": [\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:154\",\n    \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts:292-302\"\n  ],\n  \"counterevidenceSought\": \"Grepped the module for compound-key upserts, checked migration scripts, and inspected session-isolation.vitest.ts for a collision regression, none found.\",\n  \"alternativeExplanation\": \"Could be intentional single-tenant design, but REQ-024 explicitly requires session isolation, so this is rejected.\",\n  \"finalSeverity\": \"P1\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.86,\n  \"downgradeTrigger\": \"If a composite primary key `(spec_folder, loop_type, session_id, id)` lands and a collision regression covers the ID-reuse path, downgrade to P2 tech-debt.\",\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Required Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `findingId` | string | Must match the finding ID in the iteration body and registry |\n| `claim` | string | The single assertion the finding makes (one sentence, evidence-backed) |\n| `evidenceRefs` | string[] | `file:line` or `file:range` citations that substantiate the claim (at least one entry) |\n| `counterevidenceSought` | string | Where the reviewer looked for contradicting evidence (commands, paths, docs), blank string is not acceptable |\n| `alternativeExplanation` | string | An alternative reading of the evidence, even if the reviewer rejects it |\n| `finalSeverity` | `\"P0\"` \\| `\"P1\"` \\| `\"P2\"` | Severity after adjudication (may differ from the severity originally asserted) |\n| `confidence` | number `[0, 1]` | Reviewer confidence in `finalSeverity` |\n| `downgradeTrigger` | string | The concrete condition under which this finding should be downgraded in a future iteration |\n| `transitions` | object[] | Optional severity transition log, required when `finalSeverity` differs from the originally asserted severity |\n\n### Validation Rules (enforced by `step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication`)\n\n1. A packet MUST exist for every new P0/P1 finding introduced in this iteration. Carried-forward findings reuse the previous packet unless severity transitioned.\n2. All required fields MUST be present and non-empty. `confidence` MUST be a number in `[0, 1]`.\n3. Each `evidenceRefs` entry MUST contain a `:` separating the path from a line or range.\n4. `finalSeverity` MUST match the severity the finding is registered under in the iteration's `Findings` section and in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`.\n5. When any rule fails, the workflow appends `{\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"passed\":false,\"missingPackets\":[...]}` to the state log. The next `step_check_convergence` call reads that event and sets `claimAdjudicationGate` = `false`, producing a `blockedStop` event with `blockedBy: [\"claimAdjudicationGate\"]` until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packet.\n\n### Severity Transition Rules\n\n- **P2 → P1**: confirmed exploitable impact or spec violation with direct evidence\n- **P1 → P0**: demonstrated data loss, security breach, or hard-gate failure\n- **Downgrade**: requires explicit counterevidence or a confirmed alternative explanation\n- Every transition is recorded in the packet's `transitions` array and mirrored into the finding registry's `transitions` field\n\n---\n\n## 10. FINDING REGISTRY\n\nEach finding is tracked with a unique identifier enabling deduplication, severity transitions, and status lifecycle.\n\n### Schema\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findingId\": \"F003\",\n  \"severity\": \"P1\",\n  \"category\": \"resource-map-coverage\",\n  \"status\": \"active\",\n  \"dimension\": \"traceability\",\n  \"title\": \"Applied target file missing from resource-map inventory\",\n  \"file\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_start-review-loop_auto.yaml\",\n  \"line\": 955,\n  \"firstSeen\": 2,\n  \"lastSeen\": 4,\n  \"transitions\": [\n    { \"iteration\": 2, \"from\": null, \"to\": \"P2\", \"reason\": \"Initial discovery\" },\n    { \"iteration\": 4, \"from\": \"P2\", \"to\": \"P1\", \"reason\": \"Confirmed real coverage gap against applied target inventory\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| findingId | string | Sequential unique ID: `F001`, `F002`, ... |\n| severity | `\"P0\"` / `\"P1\"` / `\"P2\"` | Current severity |\n| category | `\"correctness\"` / `\"security\"` / `\"traceability\"` / `\"maintainability\"` / `\"resource-map-coverage\"` | Primary audit category for the finding, `resource-map-coverage` is reserved for implementation-vs-map coverage gaps |\n| status | `\"active\"` / `\"resolved\"` / `\"deferred\"` / `\"disproved\"` | Current status |\n| dimension | string | Primary dimension: correctness, security, traceability, maintainability |\n| title | string | Short description |\n| file | string | File path |\n| line | number | Line number (approximate) |\n| firstSeen / lastSeen | number | Iteration where first discovered / last referenced |\n| transitions | array | Severity and status change history |\n\n### Status Lifecycle\n\n```text\n[discovered] --> active --> resolved    (fixed or confirmed non-issue)\n                  |\n                  +--> deferred    (advisory, below threshold)\n                  |\n                  +--> disproved   (counterevidence invalidated)\n```\n\n| Status | Counts Toward Verdict |\n|--------|----------------------|\n| active | Yes |\n| resolved | No |\n| deferred | No (listed in Deferred Items) |\n| disproved | No |\n\n### Deduplication\n\nSame file + line range + root cause as an existing finding = **refinement**, not new. The existing findingId is updated. Refinements count at half weight (`refinementMultiplier: 0.5`) and are tracked via `findingsRefined` in JSONL.\n\n### Cross-Reference Protocols\n\n| Protocol | Level | Applies To | Gate |\n|----------|-------|------------|------|\n| spec_code | core | all types | hard |\n| checklist_evidence | core | all types | hard |\n| skill_agent | overlay | skill | advisory |\n| agent_cross_runtime | overlay | agent | advisory |\n| feature_catalog_code | overlay | skill, spec-folder, track, files | advisory |\n| playbook_capability | overlay | skill, agent, spec-folder | advisory |\n\nSeverity for `resource-map-coverage` findings is calibrated to the coverage-gate outcome:\n- `P2` when an untouched map entry is explicitly `expected-by-scope`\n- `P1` when an untouched or absent path represents a real coverage gap\n- `P0` only when the missing coverage masks a release-blocking correctness or security risk\n\n### Quality Gates\n\n| Gate | Rule |\n|------|------|\n| Evidence | Every active finding backed by concrete file:line evidence |\n| Scope | Reviewed files and conclusions stay inside declared scope |\n| Coverage | Required dimensions and required protocols covered |\n\nAll three gates must pass before STOP. Gate failure forces `verdict: \"FAIL\"` regardless of finding counts.","lineStart":241,"lineEnd":535,"totalLines":535,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1781151252985,"end":1781151252989}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08254c9624440ac9016a2a3614ec9c8191b01235449106f287"}},"id":"prt_eb4e341f0001I3ZVynXT3RPI2E","sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","messageID":"msg_eb4e3286f001R5pOJm5dL9Vtu4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781151253005,"sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wxNIHIxZiID8P3Q8AUDpgFuP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n6:   - \"review stop signals\"\n7:   - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n8:   - \"review blocked stop\"\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # Deep Review Convergence Signals\n12: \n13: This reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: Deep-review convergence is a release-readiness decision. The loop stops only when severity-weighted findings stabilize, dimension coverage is complete, quality gates pass, and no P0 override is active.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. SIGNALS\n24: \n25: | Signal | Meaning | Blocks STOP When |\n26: |--------|---------|------------------|\n27: | Severity-weighted new findings | Weighted P0/P1/P2 discovery ratio for the latest iteration | Above the configured threshold |\n28: | Rolling stop average | Stabilized trend across recent iterations | Still above the stop band |\n29: | Dimension coverage | Required review dimensions and traceability overlays covered | Any required dimension is missing |\n30: | Quality-gate bundle | Evidence, scope, coverage, P0, density, hotspot, claim, candidate, graphless gates | Any required gate fails |\n31: | Graph-aware blind spot check | Coverage graph sees unresolved structural gaps | Graph blockers remain active |\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ## 3. P0 OVERRIDE\n36: \n37: Any new P0 forces at least one more iteration. The override exists because a new blocker changes the release verdict, even if the rest of the stop math appears stable.\n38: \n39: P0 handling requires:\n40: \n41: - File and line evidence.\n42: - Adversarial self-check.\n43: - Active registry update.\n44: - Replay in synthesis before PASS is legal.\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 4. LEGAL STOP\n49: \n50: STOP is legal only when all of these are true:\n51: \n52: 1. New findings are below threshold.\n53: 2. Rolling trend is stable.\n54: 3. All required dimensions are covered.\n55: 4. The quality-gate bundle passes.\n56: 5. No unresolved P0 remains.\n57: 6. Graph-aware blockers are absent or explicitly unavailable with fallback evidence.\n58: \n59: If any item fails, the workflow emits `blocked_stop` and continues or routes to recovery.\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 5. SIBLING CONTRAST\n64: \n65: Do not carry thresholds across deep skills:\n66: \n67: | Skill | Primary Signal | Default Threshold |\n68: |-------|----------------|-------------------|\n69: | `deep-review` | Severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 new findings | `0.10` |\n70: | `deep-research` | Novelty/newInfoRatio over research knowledge | `0.05` |\n71: | `deep-ai-council` | Planning agreement with critique blocker check | Council-specific, not interchangeable |\n72: \n73: ---\n74: \n75: ## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n76: \n77: - `references/convergence/convergence.md` for the full stop contract.\n78: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` for dashboard and report fields that display convergence.\n79: - `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer-owned gate state.\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n  - \"review stop signals\"\n  - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n  - \"review blocked stop\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence Signals\n\nThis reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review convergence is a release-readiness decision. The loop stops only when severity-weighted findings stabilize, dimension coverage is complete, quality gates pass, and no P0 override is active.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review Convergence Signals\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for severity-weighted stop signals, P0 overrides, quality gates, and graph-aware blocked-stop checks.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review convergence signals\"\n  - \"review stop signals\"\n  - \"severity weighted convergence\"\n  - \"review blocked stop\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review Convergence Signals\n\nThis reference names the live stop signals. Use `references/convergence/convergence.md` as the hub when you need algorithms, examples, and sibling threshold notes.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nDeep-review convergence is a release-readiness decision. The loop stops only when severity-weighted findings stabilize, dimension coverage is complete, quality gates pass, and no P0 override is active.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SIGNALS\n\n| Signal | Meaning | Blocks STOP When |\n|--------|---------|------------------|\n| Severity-weighted new findings | Weighted P0/P1/P2 discovery ratio for the latest iteration | Above the configured threshold |\n| Rolling stop average | Stabilized trend across recent iterations | Still above the stop band |\n| Dimension coverage | Required review dimensions and traceability overlays covered | Any required dimension is missing |\n| Quality-gate bundle | Evidence, scope, coverage, P0, density, hotspot, claim, candidate, graphless gates | Any required gate fails |\n| Graph-aware blind spot check | Coverage graph sees unresolved structural gaps | Graph blockers remain active |\n\n---\n\n## 3. P0 OVERRIDE\n\nAny new P0 forces at least one more iteration. The override exists because a new blocker changes the release verdict, even if the rest of the stop math appears stable.\n\nP0 handling requires:\n\n- File and line evidence.\n- Adversarial self-check.\n- Active registry update.\n- Replay in synthesis before PASS is legal.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP\n\nSTOP is legal only when all of these are true:\n\n1. New findings are below threshold.\n2. Rolling trend is stable.\n3. All required dimensions are covered.\n4. The quality-gate bundle passes.\n5. No unresolved P0 remains.\n6. Graph-aware blockers are absent or explicitly unavailable with fallback evidence.\n\nIf any item fails, the workflow emits `blocked_stop` and continues or routes to recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 5. SIBLING CONTRAST\n\nDo not carry thresholds across deep skills:\n\n| Skill | Primary Signal | Default Threshold |\n|-------|----------------|-------------------|\n| `deep-review` | Severity-weighted P0/P1/P2 new findings | `0.10` |\n| `deep-research` | Novelty/newInfoRatio over research knowledge | `0.05` |\n| `deep-ai-council` | Planning agreement with critique blocker check | Council-specific, not interchangeable |\n\n---\n\n## 6. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `references/convergence/convergence.md` for the full stop contract.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` for dashboard and report fields that display convergence.\n- `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer-owned gate state.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":79,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","time":{"start":1781151252998,"end":1781151253004}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08254c9624440ac9016a2a3614eca48191b2ac08de4789b748"}},"id":"prt_eb4e342020015PX4Cuu051Jbrp","sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","messageID":"msg_eb4e3286f001R5pOJm5dL9Vtu4"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781151253031,"sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_J1q8JdmZZS4C2XSHFxh7hyFL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","offset":1,"limit":240},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\n3: description: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n6:   - \"review findings registry\"\n7:   - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n8:   - \"review state reconstruction\"\n9: ---\n10: \n11: # Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n12: \n13: The reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n18: \n19: The reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 2. OWNERSHIP\n24: \n25: | Surface | Writer | Rule |\n26: |---------|--------|------|\n27: | JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n28: | Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n29: | Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n30: | Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n31: | Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n32: | Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n33: \n34: No agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n39: \n40: The registry groups findings into:\n41: \n42: - Active findings.\n43: - Resolved findings.\n44: - Repeated findings.\n45: - Blocked or disputed findings.\n46: - Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n47: \n48: Each active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n53: \n54: The reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n55: \n56: Recovery order:\n57: \n58: 1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n59: 2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n60: 3. Re-run the reducer.\n61: 4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: ## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n66: \n67: When derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n68: \n69: 1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n70: 2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n71: 3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n72: 4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n73: \n74: If JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n79: \n80: The reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n81: \n82: ### Two-Tier Match\n83: \n84: 1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n85:    - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n86:    - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n87:    - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n88:    - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n89: 2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n90: \n91: ### Synthesis Behavior\n92: \n93: When the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n94: \n95: ### Emission Requirement\n96: \n97: Every finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n102: \n103: - `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n104: - `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n105: - `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n106: - `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.\n\n(End of file - total 106 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\"\ndescription: \"Focused reference for reducer ownership, findings registry semantics, fail-closed behavior, and reconstruction rules.\"\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review reducer registry\"\n  - \"review findings registry\"\n  - \"deep review reducer ownership\"\n  - \"review state reconstruction\"\n---\n\n# Deep Review State Reducer And Registry\n\nThe reducer is the single writer for derived review state. Iteration agents append evidence; the reducer reconciles it into registry, dashboard, and strategy views.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nThe reducer turns append-only review evidence into the current findings registry, dashboard, and strategy state. It is the authority for derived outputs, not a second source of truth.\n\n---\n\n## 2. OWNERSHIP\n\n| Surface | Writer | Rule |\n|---------|--------|------|\n| JSONL state | Workflow plus validated iteration append | Append-only |\n| Findings registry | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from JSONL |\n| Dashboard | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Regenerate from registry and latest events |\n| Strategy machine sections | `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Update from coverage and findings |\n| Iteration markdown | Review iteration agent | Write-once |\n| Review report | Synthesis | Final handoff |\n\nNo agent should hand-edit reducer-owned derived state as the authoritative fix. Repair JSONL or rerun the reducer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FINDINGS REGISTRY\n\nThe registry groups findings into:\n\n- Active findings.\n- Resolved findings.\n- Repeated findings.\n- Blocked or disputed findings.\n- Claim-adjudicated severity changes.\n\nEach active finding needs severity, category, file:line evidence, finding class, content hash, first-seen iteration, and latest-seen iteration.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FAIL-CLOSED BEHAVIOR\n\nThe reducer must refuse to publish derived state when JSONL is corrupt in strict mode. That protects dashboards and verdict previews from silently losing findings.\n\nRecovery order:\n\n1. Identify the malformed JSONL line.\n2. Repair or remove only the invalid appended record with an audit note.\n3. Re-run the reducer.\n4. Confirm registry and dashboard regenerate from the repaired log.\n\n---\n\n## 5. RECONSTRUCTION\n\nWhen derived files are missing but JSONL and iteration markdown exist:\n\n1. Rebuild the registry from JSONL finding details.\n2. Rebuild dashboard metrics from registry and latest convergence events.\n3. Rebuild strategy from completed dimensions and active findings.\n4. Re-run synthesis only after reducer outputs are consistent.\n\nIf JSONL is incomplete but iteration files exist, recovery is manual and must be recorded before release readiness is claimed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. FINDING DEDUPLICATION\n\nThe reducer deduplicates findings at synthesis time using a two-tier match.\n\n### Two-Tier Match\n\n1. **PRIMARY: content_hash** = `sha256(file_path + line_range + finding_type + normalized_description_80chars)`\n   - `file_path`: repo-relative path of the finding\n   - `line_range`: e.g., `\"42\"` or `\"42-56\"`\n   - `finding_type`: one of `security`, `correctness`, `performance`, `maintainability`, `test_quality`, `contract_safety`, `removal`\n   - `normalized_description_80chars`: first 80 characters of the description, whitespace-collapsed and lowercased\n2. **FALLBACK (legacy records): file:line + normalized_title** - applied when one or both records lack a `content_hash`, preserving existing behavior unchanged.\n\n### Synthesis Behavior\n\nWhen the same `content_hash` appears across iterations from different dimensions, synthesis collapses them to ONE entry with `dimensions: [<all dimensions that emitted it>]` rather than emitting multiple records. Records without `content_hash` fall back to `file:line + normalized_title`; no migration is required for existing JSONL state.\n\n### Emission Requirement\n\nEvery finding emitted into the JSONL delta (`findingDetails[]`) MUST include a `content_hash` field computed per the two-tier match. `reduce-state.cjs` reads this field for synthesis dedup.\n\n---\n\n## 7. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- `scripts/reduce-state.cjs` is the reducer implementation.\n- `references/state/state_format.md` defines state records.\n- `references/state/state_outputs.md` defines operator-visible outputs.\n- `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` defines STOP fields reducer views display.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":106,"totalLines":106,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-review/references/state/state_reducer_registry.md","time":{"start":1781151253028,"end":1781151253030}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08254c9624440ac9016a2a3614ecac8191865f187c4857aa6c"}},"id":"prt_eb4e34208001lMnE4QKrIi0Eks","sessionID":"ses_14b1d6f15ffecFZ0VCz27YhAXb","messageID":"msg_eb4e3286f001R5pOJm5dL9Vtu4"}}
